{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17626464","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17626464"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:38:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:38:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17075"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17075","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17075"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.76,0.04,0.04,0.06,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9765"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77460"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9765","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9765"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17075"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62972"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5254"},{"type":"tags","id":"5264"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22943"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23169"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77460","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77460"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ETetracycline antibiotics are broad-spectrum agents used to treat various bacterial infections.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the mechanism of action and major adverse effect of tetracyclines?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Binds to 30S ribosomal subunit and can cause permanent tooth discolouration","Inhibits bacterial DNA gyrase and can cause tendon rupture","Disrupts bacterial cell wall and can cause hearing loss","Blocks folic acid synthesis and can cause bone marrow suppression","Disrupts bacterial cell membrane and can cause kidney injury"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBinding to the 30S ribosomal subunit with risk of permanent tooth discolouration\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct answer. Tetracyclines work by binding to bacterial ribosomes and preventing protein synthesis. They also chelate calcium ions and can deposit in developing teeth and bones, causing permanent yellow-brown discolouration of teeth in children under 8 years of age.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibits bacterial DNA gyrase and can cause tendon rupture\u003C/strong\u003E describes fluoroquinolone antibiotics, which have a different mechanism of action and safety profile.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDisrupts bacterial cell wall and can cause hearing loss\u003C/strong\u003E describes aminoglycosides, which work by disrupting bacterial protein synthesis and can cause ototoxicity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocks folic acid synthesis and can cause bone marrow suppression\u003C/strong\u003E describes the mechanism and toxicity of trimethoprim, which interferes with bacterial folate metabolism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDisrupts bacterial cell membrane and can cause kidney injury\u003C/strong\u003E describes polymyxins, which act on bacterial cell membranes and can cause nephrotoxicity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDue to the risk of permanent tooth discolouration, tetracyclines are contraindicated in children under 8 years of age, during pregnancy, and in nursing mothers.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Tetracyclines work by binding to the 30S ribosomal subunit and blocking aminoacyl-tRNA binding, thereby inhibiting bacterial protein synthesis.","Tetracyclines can cause permanent tooth discolouration when given to children under 8 years of age due to calcium chelation in developing teeth.","Tetracyclines should be avoided during pregnancy and early childhood due to their effects on developing bones and teeth."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62972"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17075"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62972","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62972"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-07T07:32:42+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-07T07:37:39+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9765"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77460"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt"